---
import Base from "../../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Pet Couriers | Homeless Hounds Animal Rescue">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-600 to-purple-800 text-white py-16">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Pet Couriers</h1>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-yellow-300 font-semibold mb-6">Transport Animals to Safety</h2>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl mb-8">
            Help save lives by transporting rescued animals from foster carers to their new homes.
            Every journey you make helps an animal find their forever family.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-100 mb-8">
            <em>Homeless Hounds is registered as a charity with the Australian Charities and Not-for-profits Commission – ABN 93 136 291 221</em>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

      <!-- Why Become a Pet Courier Section -->
      <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Why should I become a pet courier?</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
          <p class="mb-6">
            Every day around Australia, hundreds of dogs, cats and other domestic animals are surrendered to animal shelters by their former owners.
            These animals are taken in by organisations like Homeless Hounds, staying with our volunteer foster carers.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-6">
            As a Homeless Hounds Pet Courier, you're volunteering to transport these dogs, cats or other animals (and any supplies)
            from their foster carer to a new home or vice versa.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-6">
            You're literally the link between an animal's rescue and their forever home. Without pet couriers, many animals wouldn't be able
            to reach their new families, especially those in regional areas or across state borders.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Where Animals Come From -->
      <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Give at-risk animals a second chance at life</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <p class="mb-4">
            Homeless Hounds takes animals from pounds and shelters, puppy and kitten farms, crisis situations
            (domestic violence, natural emergencies, homelessness etc) and other scenarios in which the animal is in danger.
          </p>
          <p>
            As we are inundated, we prioritise animals who will die without our help.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Requirements and FAQ -->
      <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
        <div class="space-y-8">

          <!-- FAQ 1 -->
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Do I need to have access to a car and insurance?</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Yes – you'll need to have access to a car and car insurance; either Third Party or Comprehensive.
              This ensures the safety of both you and the animals during transport.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ 2 -->
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What sort of animals will I be transporting?</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              You'll only transport animals you're comfortable with, including dogs, cats, rabbits and other animals.
              We'll always match you with animals that suit your experience and comfort level.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ 3 -->
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Do I need to have any equipment to be a Pet Courier?</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Ideally, you'll have a cat and/or dog carrier, and a suitable car to be able to transport the animal safely.
              If you don't have carriers, we can often provide them or help you source appropriate equipment.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ 4 -->
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">How far will I need to travel?</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Transport distances vary depending on where animals need to go. You can specify your preferred travel radius
              and we'll match requests accordingly. Some couriers help with local trips, others with longer interstate journeys.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Pet Courier Training Video -->
      <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Pet Courier Training Webinar</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <p class="mb-4">
            Watch our comprehensive training webinar to learn everything you need to know about becoming a pet courier.
            This session covers the application process, what to expect, and how to safely transport animals.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Video Embed -->
        <div class="relative w-full mb-6" style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; /* 16:9 aspect ratio */">
          <iframe
            class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full rounded-lg"
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/RcpP6OJL9Ws"
            title="How to become a Pet Courier - Webinar (October 2020)"
            frameborder="0"
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
            allowfullscreen>
          </iframe>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-green-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-3">
              <p class="text-sm text-green-700">
                <strong>Recommended:</strong> Watch this webinar before applying to get a complete understanding of the pet courier role and expectations.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Application Information -->
      <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Ready to Help Transport Animals?</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 mb-8">
          <p class="mb-4">
            Becoming a pet courier is a flexible way to help animals in need. You can choose when you're available
            and what types of transport you're comfortable with.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-6">
            The application process helps us understand your availability, vehicle type, and transport preferences
            so we can match you with suitable transport requests.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
          <div class="flex">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zm-7-4a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zM9 9a1 1 0 000 2v3a1 1 0 001 1h1a1 1 0 100-2v-3a1 1 0 00-1-1H9z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-3">
              <p class="text-sm text-blue-700">
                <strong>Application Note:</strong> The below application forms will take 3-4 minutes to complete.
                We'll contact you once your application has been reviewed.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Application CTA -->
        <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-900 mb-4">Apply Now</h4>
          <p class="text-purple-800 mb-4">
            Ready to start helping animals reach their forever homes? Apply to become a pet courier:
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
            <a href="https://homelesshounds.com.au/pet-courier-application-form/"
               target="_blank"
               class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg hover:bg-purple-700 transition-colors text-center">
              Apply to become a Pet Courier
            </a>
            <a href="/contact-us"
               class="inline-block bg-white text-purple-600 border-2 border-purple-600 font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg hover:bg-purple-50 transition-colors text-center">
              Ask Questions First
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- What Makes a Difference Section -->
      <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">How Pet Couriers Make a Difference</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-purple-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Urgent Rescues</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              Transport animals from dangerous situations to safety with our volunteer network.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-purple-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4.318 6.318a4.5 4.5 0 000 6.364L12 20.364l7.682-7.682a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364-6.364L12 7.636l-1.318-1.318a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364 0z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Happy Endings</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              Be the final link in an animal's journey from rescue to their loving forever home.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-purple-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17.657 16.657L13.414 20.9a1.998 1.998 0 01-2.827 0l-4.244-4.243a8 8 0 1111.314 0z"></path>
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 11a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Regional Reach</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              Help animals reach families in regional and remote areas who wouldn't otherwise have access.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-purple-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Flexible Timing</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              Choose when you're available and help when it suits your schedule.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Call to Action -->
      <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-600 to-purple-800 rounded-lg text-white p-8 text-center">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Be the Bridge to Their Forever Home</h3>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6">
          Every transport you complete helps an animal move one step closer to their perfect family.
          Your car can be their vehicle to happiness.
        </p>
        <p class="text-purple-200">
          Join our network of pet couriers and help make happy endings possible.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>
</Base>